The prophet Amos. Eighth century before Christ. He was a herdsman from Tekoa — not a priest, not a court prophet, a man who kept sheep and dressed sycamore trees for a living. The Lord called him north to speak to a kingdom that was rich and pleased with itself and very devout. They had their festivals. They had their music. They had their right teachings about who they were and who their God was. And Amos walked into the middle of all that and said —

